-- U.A.E. Islamic Banks Face Shariah Board Challenge, Liquidity, Suwaidi Says
-- Khalid Qayum
-- 2010-06-14T02:10:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/u-a-e-islamic-banks-face-shariah-board-challenge-liquidity-suwaidi-says.html

          
          
             Islamic banks in the United Arab
Emirates face challenges from Shariah board rulings seeking
better coordination among Islamic banks, Sultan bin Nasser al-
Suwaidi, the governor of the United Arab Emirates central bank,
said at a conference in Singapore today. Islamic banks also face
the challenge of short-term liquidity management, he said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Khalid Qayum in Singapore at 
 kqayum@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                                                 
                     
